enterprise infrastructure and telecommunications products, including telecommunications boards, consistent with an industry-wide reduction in demand for these products. the overall revenue
decline was partially offset by incremental revenue related to acquisitions completed in 2001.
net
operating results decreased by $1.1billion to a loss of $735million in 2001 from a profit of $319million in 2000, primarily due to the lower unit volumes of
microcontrollers, network processing components and telecommunications-related products. higher research and development spending in 2001 also contributed to the decline, primarily due to the expenses
of businesses acquired in 2001 and a full year of expenses for acquisitions made in 2000.
