note4: common stock repurchase program
the company has an ongoing authorization, as amended, from the board of directors to repurchase up to 2.3billion shares of intel's common stock in open
market or negotiated transactions, including the 2002 authorization to purchase an additional 480million shares. during 2002, the company repurchased 183million shares of common stock
at a cost of $4billion. since the program began in 1990, the company has repurchased and retired approximately 1.7billion shares at a cost of $30billion. as of
december28, 2002, 590million shares remained available under the repurchase authorization.
