realized marked-to-market gains (losses) on fixed income debt instruments classified as trading assets were $79million in 2002 and $(21) million in
2001. these amounts were included in interest and other, net in the consolidated statements of income. there were no debt instruments classified as trading assets in 2000.
net
realized marked-to-market gains (losses) on equity security trading assets were $57million in 2002 and $72million in 2001. the
